<DESCRIPT>  HOLIDAY; CHARITY; FOOD; HOUSING; AID; PROGRAM; ORGANIZATION; LIST  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  Needs are up sharply and donations are down this holiday season. All agencies
are able to make the most of money, which lets them buy in bulk and get volume
discounts. Here are some of their needs:; Santa Clara County  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Local  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  WHERE TO GIVE  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>     (box)CityTeam Ministries, 44 W. Julian St., San Jose; (408) 998-4770. Needs
7,000 new, unwrapped Christmas gifts ($10 to $15 value) for infants through
age 11. Bring donations to 275 N. First St. until 5 p.m., or the Julian Street
Rescue Mission until 9 p.m. Checks can be mailed to Box 143, San Jose 95103.; 
 (box)Loaves &amp; Fishes, 389 E. Santa Clara St., San Jose, behind St. Patrick's
Cathedral; (408) 293-4505. Needs turkeys and hams, canned goods, pumpkin pies,
potatoes, salad greens. Toys for infants through teen-agers. Accepting
donations weekdays from 10:30 a.m. to 7 p.m.;   (box)Sacred Heart Community
Service, 803 S. First St., San Jose 95110; (408) 283-5800. Needs rice, beans,
staples, canned goods and particularly baby formula (Similac and Enfamil, both
with iron). Also needed: bar soap, toilet paper, blankets, warm jackets,
sweaters and sweat shirts, boots and warm shoes, children's and men's
underwear of various sizes. Volunteers are needed to pack 2,800 food boxes
through Dec. 24. Call first. Open for donations 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. weekdays;
Saturday, 9 a.m. to 4 p.m.;   (box)The Salvation Army, 359 N. Fourth St., San
Jose; (408) 998-4400. Needs turkeys, hams, canned fruit and vegetables,
blankets, toys. Donations accepted at 359 N. Fourth St. on weekdays from 8
a.m. to 4 p.m., or 405 N. Fourth St. until 9:30 p.m. and weekends. Donations
are needed by Friday. Checks can be mailed to the Salvation Army, Box 2D, San
Jose 95109.;   (box)Second Harvest Food Bank of Santa Clara and San Mateo
Counties. Mail donations to 297 Commercial St., San Jose 95112; (408)
286-9170. Needs turkeys; high protein, non-perishable staples and canned
goods. Will accept donations from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m. weekdays.;   (box)St.
Joseph's Family Center, 7950A Church St., Gilroy; (408) 842-6662. Needs
canned, frozen or fresh hams and turkeys, fresh vegetables, fruit and canned
goods. Donations accepted from 9 a.m. to noon and from 1 to 4 p.m. weekdays.; 
 (box)San Jose Urban Ministry, 44 S. Fifth St., San Jose; (408) 292-4286.
Donations in adult sizes of socks, thermal underwear, scarves, hats, gloves,
coats, coffee and hams accepted weekdays from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.;  
(box)Reaching Out Food Program, Cathedral of Faith Church, 2315 Canoas Garden
Ave., San Jose 95125; (408) 723-8029. Needs money, toys, canned goods, warm
clothing and bedding.;   (box)San Jose Family Shelter, 1590 Las Plumas Ave.,
San Jose 95133; (408) 926-8885. Ask manager for current needs.;  
(box)Martha's Kitchen, 311 Willow St., San Jose 95110; (408) 293-6111. Ask for
Brother Joe or Kathy. Needs money and volunteers.;   (box)Emergency Housing
Consortium, Mail donations to Box 2346, San Jose 95109; (408) 298-9657. To
offer services or goods for pickup, call Mary Lou Jones at (408) 289-1347.
Needs blankets, towels, furniture, clothes (especially for little boys),
disposable diapers and formula, volunteer meal servers; groups to cook and
serve a meal at Gilroy, Sunnyvale or San Jose armories.; San Mateo County;  
(box)Ecumenical Hunger Program, 1934 University Ave., East Palo Alto 94303;
(415) 323-7781. Accepting turkey, hams, grocery store certificates, blankets,
toys and cash donations daily from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. through Dec. 24.;  
(box)St. Anthony's of Padua Dining Room, 3500 Middlefield Road, Menlo Park;
(415) 365-9664. Needs canned tomato products, canned and fresh vegetables,
canned hams, frozen or fresh chicken, salt, sugar, mayonnaise, beef and
chicken stock. Accepts donations Monday through Saturday from 8 a.m. to 4:30
p.m. at the dining room, or at the parish rectory until 8 p.m.; Alameda
County;   (box)Tri-City Volunteers Inc., 37350 Joseph St., Fremont; (510)
793-4583. Needs turkeys, canned hams, gifts for children and teen-agers and
the elderly. Accepting donations 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. weekdays.;  
(box)LOV-Newark, 37400 Central Court, Newark, 94560; (510) 793-5683. Needs
canned food, turkeys, hams, new unwrapped toys, and cash donations. Donations
accepted daily from 8 a.m. to 10 p.m. through Dec. 24.; Santa Cruz County;  
(box)River Street Shelter, 733 River St., Santa Cruz; (408) 425-3437. Needs
lots of blankets and sleeping bags and warm weather clothing, boots and
stockings for adults, grocery store gift certificates and staples. Donations
accepted from 3 to 9 p.m. seven days a week.  </TEXT>
